$ Excel array formulas: row and large

This example uses an → Microsoft/Office/Excel/formulas/array[array formula] to sort a range of random numbers.

The random numbers are filled into the first column. The array formula is inserted into the second column. It uses the `row()` function to create the numbers of 1 to 10 and combines
it with `large()` to get the nth largest number of the random numbers.

gh|about-Excel|/formulas/array/row/large.bas||

When run, the example produces:
gh|about-Excel|/formulas/array/row/img/large.png||

sa:

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/functions/large[`large()`]

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/formulas/array[Array formulas]
